description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Older People’s Clinical Psychologist, Band 7/8a (up to 0.6wte), Fixed term post to cover maternity leave for up to 12 months or secondment opportunity for internal applicants. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an experienced and enthusiastic Clinical Psychologist to work as part of the Pan Dorset Older People’s Clinical Psychology Service. This post involves providing specialist psychological input to clients under the care of OPCMHT’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to providing specialist psychological therapies and assessments, the provision of consultation and staff training for OPCMHT colleagues are key aspects of this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be given support to undertake CPD and receive regular clinical supervision from friendly and dedicated colleagues in the Older People’s Clinical Psychology Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be based in East Dorset .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to the development of its staff and provides training opportunities to further develop skills and supports research initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires a Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car owner/driver essential, subject to the provisions of the Equality Act (2010)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We conduct full criminal records checks on all successful candidates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMITTED TO EQUALITY AND DIVERSITY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Samantha Dench, Consultant Clinical Psychologist - Telephone: 01202 584440&lt;/p&gt;
